1054
01:20:56,960 --> 01:20:58,200
What will you do to him?

1055
01:20:59,680 --> 01:21:01,720
Poor thing,
what will they do to him?

1056
01:21:02,600 --> 01:21:05,440
Nothing. The war is over.

1057
01:21:06,040 --> 01:21:08,280
No more death, no more blood.

1058
01:21:08,680 --> 01:21:11,040
- Am I right?
- Yes, Majesty.

1059
01:21:13,960 --> 01:21:15,680
Thank you.

1060
01:21:17,280 --> 01:21:18,440
My God.

1061
01:21:28,520 --> 01:21:29,640
How are you?

1062
01:21:30,000 --> 01:21:32,600
Fine, thank God!

1063
01:21:32,960 --> 01:21:36,320
I never stopped thinking about you.

1064
01:21:37,280 --> 01:21:38,600
Dearest Pascalina...

1065
01:21:39,880 --> 01:21:42,440
you've always been in my heart.

1066
01:21:45,360 --> 01:21:47,080
What honor.

1067
01:22:06,040 --> 01:22:07,480
Ferrante!

1068
01:22:07,640 --> 01:22:09,840
Ferrante!

1069
01:22:12,000 --> 01:22:13,240
Easy there!

1070
01:22:13,480 --> 01:22:15,960
We were so worried about you!

1071
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:18,120
You crushed me!

1072
01:22:21,480 --> 01:22:22,560
Big brother!

1073
01:22:23,840 --> 01:22:26,520
- Little brother.
- You stink...

1074
01:22:26,920 --> 01:22:28,920
but you look nice with a beard.

1075
01:22:29,600 --> 01:22:31,000
Let's go home.

1076
01:22:31,600 --> 01:22:36,040
Dearest Ferrante,
we were all so concerned!

1077
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:40,040
- Bartolini, why the kisses?
- We're family now, tell him.

1078
01:22:40,240 --> 01:22:41,840
Now's not the time!

1079
01:22:42,040 --> 01:22:43,520
- Alright.
- Let's go home.

1080
01:22:43,880 --> 01:22:47,200
- Can I carry your bag?
- You'll carry nothing.

1081
01:22:48,920 --> 01:22:52,320
- What's this about "we're family"?
- Tell you later.

1082
01:22:52,560 --> 01:22:55,840
- It's not set in stone!
- I'll lead the way, enter.

1083
01:22:58,520 --> 01:23:01,320
At one point,
we see a brig pass by...

1084
01:23:01,800 --> 01:23:04,520
we get up and shout out "help"!

1085
01:23:04,880 --> 01:23:07,480
Nothing, we were on our last legs.

1086
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:11,480
When we'd lost hope,
they turned back and came to get us.

1087
01:23:11,560 --> 01:23:13,960
We were elated,
but we get on board and...

1088
01:23:14,160 --> 01:23:15,400
They were pirates!

1089
01:23:15,520 --> 01:23:18,120
The same thing happened
to my mother's uncle!

1090
01:23:19,880 --> 01:23:24,360
They sent us below deck, four days
and nights of bread and water...

1091
01:23:24,520 --> 01:23:27,520
we arrive in Algiers. You should see
how nice it is, Martino.

1092
01:23:27,600 --> 01:23:29,120
Nice!

1093
01:23:29,800 --> 01:23:32,920
Even if it was terrifying,
they took us to the medina...

1094
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:35,240
and sold us to a merchant,
Mustafa...

1095
01:23:35,680 --> 01:23:37,000
a good man!

1096
01:23:37,280 --> 01:23:40,280
He made us unload bales
of fabric day and night...

1097
01:23:40,400 --> 01:23:42,520
but we ate well together...

1098
01:23:42,720 --> 01:23:45,400
there were musicians and dancers...

1099
01:23:45,560 --> 01:23:46,920
what beauties...

1100
01:23:47,240 --> 01:23:49,760
The famous bayadere beauties, right?

1101
01:23:49,960 --> 01:23:52,720
- Would you shut up!
- I'll shut up.

1102
01:23:53,960 --> 01:23:56,920
- Who decided he's family now?
- It's not set in stone.

1103
01:23:57,760 --> 01:24:01,120
Brother, an experience
worth writing a book about.

1104
01:24:02,200 --> 01:24:04,520
- Write!
- I learned lots of Arabic words.

1105
01:24:11,960 --> 01:24:13,720
It means "My love, I love you."

1106
01:24:14,120 --> 01:24:15,680
What were you up to?

1107
01:24:19,680 --> 01:24:23,120
Shut up,
you've never even been there!

1108
01:24:23,640 --> 01:24:25,120
What's going on outside?

1109
01:24:25,480 --> 01:24:27,840
Everybody's running toward
the fortress.

1110
01:24:51,960 --> 01:24:55,000
In positions!?

1111
01:25:05,600 --> 01:25:08,160
Present arms!?

1112
01:25:12,160 --> 01:25:13,280
Brogi?

1113
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:15,360
Falaschi?

1114
01:25:15,800 --> 01:25:17,120
Foresi?

1115
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:20,400
The son of Beppe the miller.

1116
01:25:20,920 --> 01:25:23,320
- What's your name?
- Lucianino, Maestro sir.

1117
01:25:23,400 --> 01:25:24,400
- Stop it.
- That's right.

1118
01:25:24,720 --> 01:25:26,280
Aren't you ashamed?

1119
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:29,320
- The condemned cannot speak.
- Silence! Shut up!

1120
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:31,520
- He told us to be ashamed.
- Shut up!

1121
01:25:31,560 --> 01:25:35,360
You start off as bootlickers
and end up assassins.

1122
01:25:35,720 --> 01:25:38,240
Look who's talking, Maestro,
you wanted to kill!

1123
01:25:38,360 --> 01:25:41,480
Don't call me Maestro!
Did I teach you to become beasts?

1124
01:25:41,480 --> 01:25:46,520
We shouldn't kill anyone,
not even Napoleon, he's done good!

1125
01:25:46,600 --> 01:25:48,640
- Silence! Shut up!
- He's a good man.

1126
01:25:48,720 --> 01:25:50,800
Look at the good he's done to me.

1127
01:25:50,920 --> 01:25:53,600
You asked for it!

1128
01:25:54,120 --> 01:25:56,840
I agree with him,
we shouldn't hurt people.

1129
01:25:57,000 --> 01:25:59,000
Tell it to those cowards.

1130
01:25:59,400 --> 01:26:02,640
I repeated the right ideas to you
over and over...

1131
01:26:03,000 --> 01:26:07,040
but you have heads
and hearts of stone.

1132
01:26:07,120 --> 01:26:10,040
- Stop it! Stay back!
- You shut up!

1133
01:26:10,120 --> 01:26:11,400
He can't speak!

1134
01:26:11,520 --> 01:26:14,120
You think shooting people
doesn't make us suffer?

1135
01:26:14,240 --> 01:26:16,800
- We do it if it's necessary!
- Get ready!

1136
01:26:16,840 --> 01:26:20,960
Obey your commander,
that's all you know how to do.

1137
01:26:21,200 --> 01:26:25,120
- Slaves!
Prepare arms! Attention!

1138
01:26:25,160 --> 01:26:28,080
Do as he commands, you duffers!

1139
01:26:28,320 --> 01:26:31,080
Shoot, you animals, you beasts!

1140
01:26:31,320 --> 01:26:32,800
Ass-kissers!

1141
01:26:33,720 --> 01:26:35,040
What are you waiting?

1142
01:26:35,080 --> 01:26:36,040
Shoot!

1143
01:26:43,240 --> 01:26:45,360
Happy now?

1144
01:26:51,520 --> 01:26:54,960
Maestro, did you get
what you wanted?

1145
01:27:03,480 --> 01:27:05,280
No!?

1146
01:27:05,640 --> 01:27:07,400
No!?

1147
01:27:07,680 --> 01:27:08,960
Damn you all!

1148
01:27:11,280 --> 01:27:12,920
Assassins!

1149
01:27:15,720 --> 01:27:17,160
Traitor!

1150
01:27:17,560 --> 01:27:19,000
Assassin!

1151
01:27:19,200 --> 01:27:22,520
Assassin! Assassin!

1152
01:28:55,840 --> 01:28:57,120
Death to the tyrant.

1153
01:28:58,520 --> 01:28:59,680
Long live freedom.

1154
01:29:04,200 --> 01:29:05,240
He fled...

1155
01:29:05,920 --> 01:29:07,240
He fled!

1156
01:29:08,200 --> 01:29:09,720
He fled!

1157
01:29:12,240 --> 01:29:13,280
Where is he?

1158
01:29:14,960 --> 01:29:15,880
Where is he?

1159
01:29:17,640 --> 01:29:18,560
Where is he?

1160
01:29:20,440 --> 01:29:24,720
Damn him, he pretended he'd construct
roads and buildings...

1161
01:29:26,080 --> 01:29:30,720
Champagne for two!
